<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,964,1314]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">
General appearance, habitus and size of 
<taxonomicName box="[613,705,964,989]" class="Malacostraca" family="Portunidae" genus="Helenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[613,705,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">Helenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very close to that of the Neotropical genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Stal, 1862" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1862" box="[1237,1431,965,990]" class="Insecta" family="Aradidae" genus="Hesus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1237,1306,966,989]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">Hesus</emphasis>
Stål, 
<number box="[1373,1431,966,990]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" value="1862.0">1862</number>
</taxonomicName>
, both distributed in South- and Central 
<collectingCountry box="[578,678,1001,1026]" name="United States of America" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">America</collectingCountry>
. Usinger &amp; Matsuda, 
<number box="[920,976,1002,1026]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" value="1959.0">1959</number>
published detailed redescriptions of both genera (
<taxonomicName box="[242,311,1038,1061]" class="Insecta" family="Aradidae" genus="Hesus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[242,311,1038,1061]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">Hesus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
p. 
<number box="[345,390,1038,1062]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" value="368.0">368</number>
; 
<taxonomicName box="[402,494,1036,1061]" class="Malacostraca" family="Portunidae" genus="Helenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[402,494,1036,1061]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">Helenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
p. 
<number box="[528,571,1037,1062]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" value="369.0">369</number>
) which need not to be repeated here.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,964,1314]" box="[199,1437,1073,1098]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">
The distinguishing characters are given in their key for the “American Genera of 
<taxonomicName box="[1105,1220,1073,1098]" class="Insecta" family="Aradidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Mezirinae">Mezirinae</taxonomicName>
” p. 
<number box="[1266,1308,1074,1098]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" value="203.0">203</number>
as follows:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,964,1314]" box="[199,1436,1109,1134]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">• Body covered with shaggy, erect pubescence. Pronotum without anterolateral lobes. Head without rounded</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,964,1314]" box="[195,575,1145,1170]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">
postocular lobes = 
<taxonomicName authority="White" authorityName="White" box="[407,575,1145,1170]" class="Malacostraca" family="Portunidae" genus="Helenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[407,499,1145,1170]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">Helenus</emphasis>
White
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,964,1314]" box="[199,1436,1181,1206]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">• Body not pubescent. Pronotum with brief anterolateral lobes bent inward to anterior collar. Head with</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,964,1314]" box="[195,624,1217,1242]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">
rounded postocular lobes. = 
<taxonomicName authority="Stal" authorityName="Stal" box="[506,624,1217,1242]" class="Insecta" family="Aradidae" genus="Hesus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[506,575,1218,1241]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">Hesus</emphasis>
Stål
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,964,1314]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">
The most recent summaries of published records of these genera are given by Heiss, 
<number box="[1115,1171,1254,1278]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" value="2009.0">2009</number>
(Review of 
<taxonomicName box="[1311,1379,1254,1277]" class="Insecta" family="Aradidae" genus="Hesus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1311,1379,1254,1277]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">Hesus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and Coscaron &amp; Contreras, 
<number box="[415,471,1290,1314]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" value="2012.0">2012</number>
(Catalog of the 
<taxonomicName box="[653,756,1289,1314]" class="Insecta" family="Aradidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Aradidae</taxonomicName>
for the Neotropical Region).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
