<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1467,1723]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">
<number box="[151,163,1467,1489]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" value="1.0">1</number>
(
<number box="[176,189,1467,1489]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" value="4.0">4</number>
) Body surface covered with dense shaggy pubescence consisting of shorter yellowish adpressed hairs intermixed with longer erect setae; pe-angles of lateral margins of deltg II–VI not or inconspicuously protruding (Figs.1,6,7).................. 
<geoCoordinate pageId="1" pageNumber="556">
<number box="[1424,1436,1496,1518]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" value="2.0">2</number>
<number box="[151,163,1525,1547]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" value="2.0">2</number>
</geoCoordinate>
(
<number box="[177,189,1525,1547]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" value="3.0">3</number>
) Pilosity generally more dense, exposed part of male pygophore wide and conical posteriorly, its median dorsal elevation anteriorly depressed along longitudinal suture, raised laterally (
<figureCitation box="[792,844,1555,1577]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1702,1723]" captionTargetBox="[158,1410,205,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,193,1681]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 10. Helenus spp.: 6 — Helenus wachteli n. sp., holotype male, dorsal view; 7 — Helenus wachteli n. sp., paratype female, dorsal view; 8 – 10. Male pygophore: 8 — hesiformis; 9 — hirsutus; 10 — wachteli n. sp." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255981/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">
Fig. 
<number box="[833,844,1555,1577]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
), parameres more slender (
<figureCitation box="[1104,1166,1555,1577]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 — 13" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1300,1321]" captionTargetBox="[278,1308,689,1274]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[270,1316,681,1278]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 11 — 13. Left paramere of Hesus spp.: 11 — hesiformis; 12 — hirsutus; 13 — wachteli n. sp." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255982/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">
Fig. 
<number box="[1144,1166,1555,1577]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
)....... 
<taxonomicName authority="White" authorityName="White" box="[1271,1436,1555,1577]" class="Malacostraca" family="Portunidae" genus="Helenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hesiformis">
<emphasis box="[1271,1371,1556,1577]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">hesiformis</emphasis>
White
</taxonomicName>
<number box="[151,163,1584,1606]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" value="3.0">3</number>
(
<number box="[176,189,1584,1606]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" value="2.0">2</number>
) Pilosity generally less dense, exposed part of male pygophore wide and truncate posteriorly, its median dorsal elevation keellike (
<figureCitation box="[275,339,1613,1635]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1702,1723]" captionTargetBox="[158,1410,205,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,193,1681]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 10. Helenus spp.: 6 — Helenus wachteli n. sp., holotype male, dorsal view; 7 — Helenus wachteli n. sp., paratype female, dorsal view; 8 – 10. Male pygophore: 8 — hesiformis; 9 — hirsutus; 10 — wachteli n. sp." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255981/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">
Fig. 
<number box="[315,339,1613,1635]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
), parameres with wider body (
<figureCitation box="[632,695,1613,1635]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 — 13" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1300,1321]" captionTargetBox="[278,1308,689,1274]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[270,1316,681,1278]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 11 — 13. Left paramere of Hesus spp.: 11 — hesiformis; 12 — hirsutus; 13 — wachteli n. sp." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255982/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">
Fig. 
<number box="[672,695,1613,1635]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
)................................................. 
<taxonomicName box="[1293,1374,1614,1635]" class="Malacostraca" family="Portunidae" genus="Helenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wachteli" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1293,1374,1614,1635]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">wachteli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1382,1436,1614,1636]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1382,1436,1614,1636]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
<number box="[151,163,1643,1665]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" value="4.0">4</number>
(
<number box="[178,187,1643,1665]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" value="1.0">1</number>
) Body surface granulate, yellowish adpressed hairs intermixed with erect setae less dense and more dispersed; pe-angles of lateral margins of deltg II–VI distinctly protruding (
<figureCitation box="[700,753,1672,1694]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1938,1959]" captionTargetBox="[188,1425,245,1897]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,195,1913]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Helenus spp.: 1 — Helenus hesiformis, holotype male, dorsal view; 2 — Helenus hirsutus, lectotype male, dorsal view; 3 — labels attached to holotype of hesiformis; 4 — ditto, reverse side; 5 — labels attached to holotype of hirsutus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255980/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">
Fig. 
<number box="[740,753,1672,1694]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
); (exposed part of male pygophore triangular narrowly conical posteriorly, median dorsal elevation keel-like (
<figureCitation box="[606,659,1701,1723]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1702,1723]" captionTargetBox="[158,1410,205,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,193,1681]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 10. Helenus spp.: 6 — Helenus wachteli n. sp., holotype male, dorsal view; 7 — Helenus wachteli n. sp., paratype female, dorsal view; 8 – 10. Male pygophore: 8 — hesiformis; 9 — hirsutus; 10 — wachteli n. sp." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255981/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">
Fig. 
<number box="[647,659,1701,1723]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
), parameres slender (
<figureCitation box="[863,925,1701,1723]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 — 13" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1300,1321]" captionTargetBox="[278,1308,689,1274]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[270,1316,681,1278]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 11 — 13. Left paramere of Hesus spp.: 11 — hesiformis; 12 — hirsutus; 13 — wachteli n. sp." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255982/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">
Fig. 
<number box="[902,925,1701,1723]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
))......................... 
