<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1768,1820]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,210,1768,1789]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">Note:</emphasis>
Because of variable colouration, size and density of pilosity, females of 
<taxonomicName box="[950,1055,1768,1790]" class="Malacostraca" family="Portunidae" genus="Helenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hesiformis">
<emphasis box="[950,1055,1768,1790]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">hesiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1105,1191,1768,1790]" class="Malacostraca" family="Portunidae" genus="Helenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wachteli" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1105,1191,1768,1790]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">wachteli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1198,1255,1768,1789]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1198,1255,1768,1789]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can not presently be separated with certainty. The male genitalic structures are distinctive for the three species.
</paragraph>
